<item>
            <title>[LU-3495] Count the request rates of ptlrpc services</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3495</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The statistics of request rates of ptlrpc services in real time is always helpful for us to understand the status of the system. Job Stats(&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-694&quot; title=&quot;Job Stats&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-694&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-694&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) might help a lot in some cases. But we might need some other simple, lightweight mechanism to collect the information as an alternate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch that we will push in a few minutes is a simple algorithm which can help to calculate the request rate between different time intervals. It really helps us a lot to monitor how NRS policies act.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
